65 PositionVelocity::PositionVelocity(const fastrack_msgs::State& msg)
66  : State(),
67  position_(Vector3d::Zero()),
68  velocity_(Vector3d::Zero()) {
69  // Check dimensions.
70  if (msg.x.size() != StateDimension())
71  throw std::runtime_error("PositionVelocity: incorrect msg dimension.");
72 
73  position_(0) = msg.x[0];
74  position_(1) = msg.x[1];
75  position_(2) = msg.x[2];
76  velocity_(0) = msg.x[3];
77  velocity_(1) = msg.x[4];
78  velocity_(2) = msg.x[5];
79 }
80 PositionVelocity::PositionVelocity(const VectorXd& config)
81  : State(),
82  position_(Vector3d::Zero()),
83  velocity_(Vector3d::Zero()) {
84  // Check dimensions.
85  if (config.size() != ConfigurationDimension())
86  throw std::runtime_error("PositionVelocity: incorrect config dimension.");
87 
88  position_(0) = config(0);
89  position_(1) = config(1);
90  position_(2) = config(2);
91 }

93 // Static function to sample from the configuration space associated
94 // with this state space. Pass in the lower and upper bounds from
95 // which to sample.
96 VectorXd PositionVelocity::Sample() {
97  const size_t kConfigurationSpaceDimension = 3;
98 
99  // Make sure bounds are of the right size.
100  if (lower_.size() != kConfigurationSpaceDimension ||
101  upper_.size() != kConfigurationSpaceDimension) {
102  throw std::runtime_error("PositionVelocity: invalid configuration space bounds.");
103  }
104 
105  // Initialize a uniform random distribution in (0, 1).
106  std::uniform_real_distribution<double> unif(0.0, 1.0);
107 
108  // Generate random sample.
109  VectorXd sample(kConfigurationSpaceDimension);
110  for (size_t ii = 0; ii < kConfigurationSpaceDimension; ii++)
111  sample(ii) = lower_(ii) + (upper_(ii) - lower_(ii)) * unif(rng_);
112 
113  return sample;
114 }

116 // For a given configuration, what are the corresponding positions in
117 // position space that the system occupies.
118 // NOTE! For simplicity, this is a finite set. In future, this could
119 // be generalized to a collection of generic obstacles.
120 std::vector<Vector3d> PositionVelocity::OccupiedPositions() const {
121  return std::vector<Vector3d>({ position_ });
122 }

124 // Set bounds of the configuration space.
125 void PositionVelocity::SetConfigurationBounds(
126  const VectorXd& lower, const VectorXd& upper) {
127  // Catch incorrect dimensions.
128  if (lower.size() != ConfigurationDimension() ||
129  upper.size() != ConfigurationDimension())
130  throw std::runtime_error("PositionVelocity: incorrect bound dimensions.");
131 
132  lower_ = lower;
133  upper_ = upper;
134 }

136 // Convert to ROS message.
137 fastrack_msgs::State PositionVelocity::ToRos() const {
138  fastrack_msgs::State msg;
139  msg.x.push_back(position_[0]);
140  msg.x.push_back(position_[1]);
141  msg.x.push_back(position_[2]);
142  msg.x.push_back(velocity_[0]);
143  msg.x.push_back(velocity_[1]);
144  msg.x.push_back(velocity_[2]);
145 
146  return msg;
147 }
